Description: Fragment of a pottery black figure amphora; handle and part of shoulder; black glaze on handle much worn; black-figure decoration on shoulder, of which only a small part is preserved to left of handle (wings?). Hard, bright red clay, Munsell 2.5YR 6/6 (light red); silver mica.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 339)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
